defaultTaiwan
default or somewhere, it is more difficult to engage with them.  Localness in the 
defaultUK
default sense is good.  The scale and experience of their history with R and D is important.  If one went today to GlaxoSmithKline, or one of these big research-intensive companies—Rolls-Royce—they have been doing this for a very long time, they understand it and they are fully engaged.  They know what they want, you can work with them and you can develop the paradigm.  
defaultIf one goes to—I should not really pick on individual companies—a company that is, let us say, not so familiar with industrial research, it is a much harder game, because you are not 
